As the clients of foobar.com increases, it will be great to have specialized servers to handle each aspect of the 
web infrastructure.

The application server, webserver, and database sever are separated from each other to allow for scaling when the time
for adding new web devices arrives.

Scaling web infrastructure is a part of all well drafted web services. At some point, more web devices would be needed
and a great way to scale is to separate the functions of the servers.
